<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-22-0546 </DOCNO><TEXT>The impact of exchange rate fluctuations on the ability of OPEC to stabilizethe oil market is assessed. Since oil prices are denominated in US dollars,changes in the exchange rate parity influence the cost of imported oilof major European countries and Japan, which in turn influences the demandfor oil and eventually demand for OPEC oil. These variations become importantfactors for the stability of the market when OPEC output is at eithermaximum or minimum limits of the Organization's production capacity.</TEXT></DOC>